main event: A civilian rancher observed three silver, cigar-shaped objects in Fossil, Oregon on July 6, 1965 for a duration of 2 minutes.
interesting points: The objects were 60 ft long and 12 ft in depth., They moved at a slow speed and disappeared suddenly., The observation was categorized as ground-visual., There was no physical evidence provided., The Air Force was unable to evaluate the report due to insufficient information.
